[SN]TITLE[SN]
Three London flat fires force 100 people out of homes

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
About 100 people had to flee three separate fires which broke out in London in the space of an hour.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Fifty people were forced out of their homes by a blaze at a residential building in Spring Street, Paddington just after 22:00 BST on Saturday.
Crews were then called to a fire at a flat in York Rise, Kentish Town, causing 40 people to be evacuated.
Firefighters were then called to another flat fire in Belmont Street, Chalk Farm, at 22:43 BST.
A London Fire Brigade spokesman said no injuries were reported.
